I found that the classpath of the project did not contain the Axis JARs copied 
into the WebContent/WEB-INF/lib directory (defect 90515).  To workaround the 
problem, we put the JARs in WEB-INF/lib explicitely in the classpath passed to 
Java2WsdlAntTask (in ClasspathUtils).  However, the NoClassDefFound problem 
still would not go away when hitting Next on page 4:

Emitter emitter = new Emitter();

where it's constructing a new org.apache.axis.wsdl.fromJava.Emitter.

One other problem is the classes in JavaSource directory is not compiled into 
WEB-INF/classes directory.  So the Java2WsdlAntTask would have problem loading 
the service bean as well (defect 90560).
